# Investor Quest = premium gamified research (NOT a dashboard)

## Product feeling to reinforce
- Curiosity, exploration, progression, achievement, mastery, confidence.
- Frame actions as **unlocking knowledge**, **building conviction**, **leveling up** (not “reading reports”).

## Visual + interaction style
- Premium fintech game: dark sci‑fi, glassmorphism/holographic UI, neon violet energy, subtle blue accents, cinematic glow.
- Smooth, responsive, rewarding micro-interactions (hover/click states feel alive, not flashy).
- Avoid: spreadsheet layouts, flat corporate dashboard UI, bright white surfaces, generic SaaS cards.

## Animation rules
- Subtle + premium: glow pulses, gentle float, soft particle drift, smooth scaling.
- Avoid: excessive bouncing, cluttered motion, “cheap” effects.

## Interaction layering (critical)
- **All important elements must stay clickable/mobile-friendly.**
- Decorative layers must never intercept input: apply `pointer-events: none` to routes SVG, particles, glow overlays, gradients, nexus FX, fog/vignette layers.
- Keep the interactive node/card layer above routes/FX (explicit `z-index` / stacking context).

## Tech constraints (hydration-safe)
- No `Math.random()` during render; no time-based randomness on first paint.
- No browser-only measurements during SSR; gate client-only logic in effects.
- Avoid layout shift; keep mobile-first responsiveness.
